Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Euthanasia and the terminally ill
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yjvwt
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 5 Apr 1996
Euthanasia, and the right to die for the terminally ill, the case of Karen Ann Quinlan, and Dr Jack Kevorkian, the Michigan doctor who has helped 27 dying people.